title: Dozens Of Birds Displaced And Orphaned During Land Clearing For Renewable Power Project | 10 News+
description: A regional Australian community is expressing outrage over a mass tree clearing during bird breeding season, as part of works to make way for a major renewable energy project. At least fifty baby birds – including rosellas, kookaburras and parrots – were displaced and orphaned during the vegetation removal that took place near Mudgee, in New South Wales.
